## Node Structure:
- `nodespec.yaml` вЂ” the ONLY file at root level (schema-validated, everything the platform needs to know)
- `profile/` вЂ” ALL other files:
  - `profile/run.sh` вЂ” Execution script (REQUIRED)
  - `profile/<software>.inp.template` вЂ” Input template (Python string.Template syntax: $var)
  - `profile/<helper>.py` вЂ” Python helper scripts
  - `profile/<data>.json` вЂ” Data/config files

CRITICAL: Only nodespec.yaml at root. Everything else in profile/.

## nodespec.yaml Key Rules:
- `metadata.name`: kebab-case, software-prefixed (e.g. '{{ software | default("gaussian") }}-freq')
- `metadata.node_type`: Must be `compute` (execution via run.sh)
- `metadata.base_image_ref`: name from Available Docker Images list (e.g. `g16`, `orca-6.1`)
- `metadata.semantic_type`: key from semantic_registry.yaml, or `Undefined` if nothing fits
- `stream_inputs/outputs`: snake_case port names. io_type.category: physical_quantity / software_data_package / logic_value / report_object
- `onboard_inputs`: user parameters (kind: string / integer / float / boolean / enum / textarea)
- `onboard_outputs`: result values shown in UI. Can have quality_gate (must_pass / warning_only)
- `resources`: cpu_cores, mem_gb, estimated_walltime_hours, ...
- `resources.parametrize`: list of resource fields в†’ auto-generates OnBoardInput controls
- `execution`: `{}` for standard compute nodes (run.sh handles everything)

## run.sh Key Rules:
- Start with `# MF2 init` on its own line (after `set -euo pipefail`). Compiler replaces this with `source /mf/profile/mf2_init.sh`, which provides:
  - `${INPUT_DIR}`, `${OUTPUT_DIR}`, `${WORKDIR}`, `${PROFILE_DIR}`, `${WORKSPACE_DIR}`
  - `mf_param "name" "default"` вЂ” read onboard parameter, return default if missing
  - `mf_banner "name" "desc"` вЂ” startup banner with node ID and UTC timestamp
  - `mf_write_xyz "$geometry" "name"` вЂ” write XYZ geometry to ${WORKDIR}/input.xyz [дёґж—¶жЂ§зљ„пјЊеЏЄйЂ‚з”ЁдєЋxyzиѕ“е…Ґ]
  - **Auto param loading**: all onboard_inputs AND resources.parametrize entries are auto-loaded as shell variables via mf_node_params.sh. Use `$charge`, `$basis_set`, `$n_cores` directly вЂ” no need to call mf_param for each.
  - ERR trap dumps tail of output.log on non-zero exit for debugging
- Read stream inputs from `${INPUT_DIR}/<port_name>`
- Write stream outputs to `${OUTPUT_DIR}/<port_name>`
- Use `${WORKDIR}` for intermediate files
- Generate software input files using Python heredoc + string.Template
- NOT jinja2 in templates вЂ” use Python `$var` / `${var}` only. Conditional logic goes in run.sh's Python heredoc.

